Product description

  • How to connect the smart watch to the phone?

    Download Da Fit APP from Google Play/APP Store or scan the QR code on the manual or in the watch settings, activate the Bluetooth on your phone.

  • What should I do if my smartwatch does not turn on?

    For first time use, please charge the product for 3-4 hours until fully charged, the product will turn on by itself during charging.

  • How do I change my watch dial?

    Rotate the gear on the right side of the screen to switch dials. While connected, open the app and tap Device, you can find the dial settings, choose your favorite dial, download and change it. You can also choose photo, customize dial.

  • Why don't smartwatches record steps?

    To enable step tracking, simply shake the watch to activate the vibration sensors and start counting your steps.

  • Why the watch fails to receive notifications from smartphone?

    Make sure to disable DND (Do-Not-Disturb) mode on your watch and ensure that your phone's notification bar is displaying messages. Additionally, check if the notification function is enabled on the DaFit" app.

      5.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
      It has a good battery and it is comfortable on my wrist
      Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2024
      I ordered this watch from Amazon Vine, and I have been using it for two weeks now. Right out of the box, I was impressed with how sleek the design looked. It has a nice curved touch screen that is pretty responsive, and I like that it has multiple watch faces for me to... See more
      I ordered this watch from Amazon Vine, and I have been using it for two weeks now. Right out of the box, I was impressed with how sleek the design looked. It has a nice curved touch screen that is pretty responsive, and I like that it has multiple watch faces for me to choose from, which I could customize in the app. It is not often that I get to personalize things that much, so that was a cool little touch for me.

      It feels comfortable on my wrist so I dont have any problems wearing it daily. The silicone band is soft, and I barely notice it after a while. The fitness tracking is spot on, I mainly use it when I go running, and I appreciate how it tracks my steps, calories, and heart rate during my workouts. I can see all the data on my watch easily without having to go through too many screens, which is important when I am in the middle of a workout.

      The call and message features are something I didnt expect to use much, but now I kind of rely on them to stay connected while I am keeping my phone tucked away. The battery life is also pretty good, as it lasts me a little bit over two days, I have been putting it to charge on the third day, even though I use it to track my workouts, I receive notifications all the time, so I am pretty surprised that the battery lasts that long. Overall, I am happy with this watch.
